een the white hosts and the ethnic guests to illustrate U.S. aspirations for global power through the medium of television. These depictions of racial harmony aimed to shape a new perception of the United States as an exemplary nation of democracy, equality, and globalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aAsian Americans on television. 0aCold WarxInfluence. 0aHispanic Americans on television. 0aVariety shows (Television programs)zUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aethnic spectacle, asian, latin american, Cold War, Korean War, Cuban Revolution, statehood of Hawaii, US internationalism, communism, television variety show, The Xavier Cugat Show, The Ed Sullivan Show, The Chevy Show, white host, ethnic guest, democracy, equality, globalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069033040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9781978803879?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978803879423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978803879/original  a978-3-11-069033-0  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070478-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design